msgid "Setting up a &kvm; &vmhost;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_host_installation.xml:14
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section documents how to set up and use &productname; &productnumber; as a &qemu;-&kvm; based virtual machine host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_host_installation.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid "Resources"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_host_installation.xml:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "In general, the virtual guest system needs the same hardware resources as if it were installed on a physical machine. The more guests you plan to run on the host system, the more hardware resources&mdash;CPU, disk, memory, and network&mdash;you need to add to the &vmhost;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: qemu_host_installation.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "CPU support for virtualization"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_host_installation.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "To run &kvm;, your CPU must support virtualization, and virtualization needs to be enabled in BIOS. The file <filename>/proc/cpuinfo</filename> includes information about your CPU features."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: qemu_host_installation.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "To find out whether your system supports virtualization, see <xref linkend=\"sec-kvm-requires-hardware\"/> ."
